### List sidecars for process

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/processes/[guid]/sidecars \
  -X GET \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]"
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :paginated_list_of_sidecars, '/v3/processes/ccc25a0f-c8f4-4b39-9f1b-de9f328d0ee5/sidecars' %>
```

Retrieves all sidecars associated with a process.

#### Definition
`GET /v3/processes/:process_guid/sidecars`

#### Query Parameters

Name | Type | Description
---- | ---- | ------------
**page** | _integer_ | Page to display. Valid values are integers >= 1.
**per_page** | _integer_ | Number of results per page. <br>Valid values are 1 through 5000.
**order_by** | _string_ | Value to sort by. Defaults to ascending. Prepend with `-` to sort descending. <br>Valid values are `created_at`, `updated_at`.

